p: There were decreases in projected spinifex cover ( figure 3 a) and the spinifex seed index ( figure 3 b) over the next 100 years, but not in the mean projected rodent captures from changes in rainfall and wildfire patterns ( figure 3 c). When introduced predators were removed from the models, there was an increase in predicted rodent captures of approximately 9%. However, when both native and non-native mammalian predators were removed, rodent captures were projected to increase by approximately 3% ( figure 3 c).
